(67, 'Plateau State', '2023062909130376.png', '<p>&nbsp;In 2022, we began a partnership with EMS of ECWA, the mission department of the Evangelical Church Winning All (ECWA) that is saddled with the responsibilities of reaching the un-reached and un-churched nations of the world with the gospel of Jesus Christ. Presently the biggest indigenous and denominational mission agency in 19 Countries in Africa, the Middle East, Europe and the USA with 3, 500 Missionaries, EMS has a rich and formidable network of mission fields catering to the needs of many congregations and communities in the world. This partnership has placed our Founder as the Principal of the oldest and biggest EMS Children&rsquo;s School located in Jos and secondly has given us a platform to work with other school administrators to ensure that the other 39 EMS schools function as they should. We are working with a network of 40 schools, 188 staff and 2,890 school children spread across typical hard-to-reach rural communities in Northwest Nigeria all in our commitment to take quality education to children in rural and disadvantaged communities. The EMS Children&rsquo;s School Jos as a boarding facility caters for 368 children of missionaries who come from 352 typical hard-to-reach rural communities spread across 16 states of Nigeria. We have set up a school management system, were part of an outreach to rural settlements in Southwest Nigeria, initiated the Vacation Bible School for students, initiated the Prefects Leadership Retreat alongside a Student Council, launched the Business Summit for Schools and initiated the observance of National and International Days among others. We have also initiated awareness campaigns to religious organizations and churches to raise support for the school and have partnered with other Non-Profits to carry out projects at the school.</p>\r\n', '', '', '', 'WORK', 1, 1, '2023-06-22 14:58:42'),
(66, 'Swanta Blessing Bonat', '202306290553013.png', '<p style=\"text-align:left\">Swanta is the Founder and Executive Director of Community Outreach for Educational Change. Popularly known as Tr. Swanta, she is an educator with special interests in children development. She loves children and has been dedicated to the cause of ensuring that children acquire quality education, particularly children from rural areas. Prior to Community Outreach for Educational Change, Swanta worked as a Hostel Administrator at Africa International College, Abuja.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:left\">Armed with a B A in Education (CRS), a Masters degree in Christian Education and certified with the Teachers Registration Council of Nigeria, she has a vast experience working at all levels of education and school systems. Her career started as a Class Assistant after which she rose through the ranks of being a Class Teacher, House Mistress, Hostel Administrator, School Administrator and now a School Manager. She has also undergone series of trainings and workshops which have given her the license to dare the odds in the profession.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:left\">In her journey to contribute to the education sector in Nigeria and in her approach to be the change she sought to see, she resigned her job and left the city of Abuja to pursue active educational evangelism &ndash; taking basic education to underserved and unreached communities. She founded Community Outreach for Educational Change- COEC in 2016 to enable her accomplish the singular goal of reaching more children with quality education regardless of their ethnicity, religion, location, social status, political affiliation or age.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:left\">Swanta uses her social media platforms to inspire sacrifice and educational activism amongst many of her followers through the detailed narrations of her experiences in the various schools and educational interventions she has been involved with. A journey through her Public School Experience and HeadTeacherDiaries series on Facebook will leave you drawn into the plight of the many school children in rural and disadvantaged communities. Through these narrations, many school children in rural communities have been reached. Swanta has spoken on radio, television and at events and been part of outreaches to over twenty-one typical rural communities in North-West Nigeria to create awareness of the importance of education. In recognition of her contributions as a teacher and especially as a school leader who worries about the welfare of her staff and students Swanta has earned features in more than 10 online magazines, blogs, and pages of Facebook, Instagram and Twitter by various organizations and individuals with several awards like the FBI Award for Influence through Professionalism, 2020, the AKS Education Awards India for Global Teacher Award, 2020, the FBI Award for Influence through Education/Social Good, 2019, the ZI Prize Award for Education and Activism, 2019 and the NBTT Recognition Award of the Year 2017 in Honor of Continuous Contribution &amp; Support towards Literacy and Language Development. In 2023, she received the Inspirational Educator Award as the 2023 Inspirational Leader of the Year from Meadow Hall Foundation for the work she does with schools and children in hard to reach communities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:left\">Swanta is currently the Principal of the oldest and biggest EMS Children&rsquo;s School located in Jos and also serves on the board of Thinking Cap Literacy Initiative another NGO whose main goal is to roll back illiteracy among Nigerian children and teenagers using various creative methods.</p>\r\n', 'Founder/Executive Director', '', '', 'TEAM1', 0, 1, '2023-06-22 14:56:04'),
(68, 'Mark Paul Amaza ', '202306290552102.png', '<p style=\"text-align:left\">Mark Amaza is a sustainable development professional currently working in circulareconomy, specifically used-battery management and recycling.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:left\">He has previously worked inoff-grid renewable energy access and sustainable development policy.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:left\">He is a co-founder of MINDcapital, a brands and strategy firm.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:left\">Mark is passionate about youth development through education, entrepreneurship and political participation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:left\">Besides serving on the board of the Community Outreach for Educational Change, he is also a member of the Strategy Team of the Not Too Young To RunMovement, which seeks to increase youth political participation in Nigeria.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:left\">He holds a degree in Environmental Management from the Abubakar Tafawa Balewa University, Bauchi.</p>\r\n', 'Board Member', '', '', 'TEAM1', 0, 1, '2023-06-22 15:01:48'),
(69, 'Onoviran Orimisan Onoviran', '202306290552311.png', '<p style=\"text-align:left\">Onoviran has over 17 years of banking experience especially in Marketing. He has worked in Kano, Sokoto, Niger and Kaduna States as both Head of Marketing and Branch Manager. He has headed various marketing units in Northern Nigeria.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:left\">A graduate of International Studies of the prestigious Ahmadu Bello University Zaria, he proceeded the Usmanu Danfodio University Sokoto where he obtained a Masters in Public Administration.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:left\">He has done various trainings in Credit analysis, Accounting/Financial analysis, High Performance Sales, Operational Risk, Sustainability, Environmental and Social Risk Management.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:left\">He is a passionate voice for equitable access to a better world through quality education and sustainable innovation in Nigeria which made him establish his own NGO to reach out to young people in primary and post primary schools with quality education. He is an outspoken education advocate and has used the powerful tool of advocacy and community engagement to speak out for quality education so as to bring change to the Nigerian system of education.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:left\">He also serves on the board of EE&amp;M Integrated a Micro- Credit company as a Financial Consultant.</p>\r\n', 'Board Member', '', '', 'TEAM1', 0, 1, '2023-06-22 15:02:41'),
(70, 'Philip Hayab John', '20230629052803Phil.png', '<p style=\"text-align:left\">Philip is a teacher educator with strong experience strengthening pre-service and in-service teachers&rsquo; capacity, developing teaching, and learning resources to strengthen learner-centred pedagogy. In addition to being a teacher educator, Philip provides education development and technical support as a Master Trainer, Educational Facilitator, Consultant and Education Quality Assurance (EQA) Advisor, enabling best classroom practices for improvements and better-quality learning outcomes, supporting the British Council, UNICEF, UBEC, NSF Developments Ltd - World Bank-led programmes and DFID funded projects. Equally, Philip has a catalogue of publications on Language Teaching and Development and speaks at conferences and the community level promoting a multilingual approach to teaching and instruction.</p>\r\n', 'Chair, COEC Schools Governing Board', '', '', 'TEAM1', 0, 1, '2023-06-22 15:03:32'),
